args: Ahhh... Bliss! Few things beat a nice walk\non the beach.
I'm inclined to agree. The sound of the\nwaves breaking on the shore is soothing.
Oh, er, I'm fine. That sudden wave\njust surprised me, that's all.
Are you afraid of the ocean, Mym?
Well, yes... A little. After what happened,\nI mean.
That's right, you almost drowned out there.
Come here. We'll keep a little more\ndistance between us and the water's\nedge.
(Oh... He's pulling me by the hand again.)
(What should I do? My darling is grappling\nwith the aftermath of his memory loss...)
(But I can't deny I'm thrilled to be the\nrecipient of his undivided attention.)
What do you suppose is going on over\nthere, Mym? A bunch of people seem to\nbe making something.
Let's get a little closer and see!
Pardon me. May I ask what you're making?
Why, hello, stranger.\nThis is a wishing crystal.
Hm. First I've heard of such a thing.
That so? It's a yearly tradition around these\nparts to float these crystals into the air.
And they say that once they're up and\naway, all the wishes in the crystal will\ncome true! You're welcome to join in.
It sounds like a lovely event. Mym,\nshould we try making a crystal, too?
...that my darling would have eyes only\nfor me.
I... Thank you. I'm really glad you're here.
(But I can't deny I'm thrilled to be the\nrecipient of his undivided attention.)
Could all of this be because of that wish?
Is something wrong, Mym?\nYou don't look so good.
Oh, no, everything's fine! I just need\nto go powder my nose. Back in a flash!
Heh. Don't think too hard about it, lad.
Hey, mister! We'll teach you how to make\nthe crystals while you wait for your lady\nfriend to come back!
Hey! Crystal faerie! Where are you?
I'm guessing that since you came here,\nyour wish came true.
Yeah, and now we're in a dilly of a pickle!
Hmmm... So your wish for the prince to\n＂have eyes only for you＂ has caused him\nto have amnesia.
That's right. Because of me,\nmy darling is—
So my crystals can grant dragon wishes\ntoo... This is an incredible discovery!
Forgive me. I wasn't actually certain the\ncrystal I gave you—a dragon—would work.
I know it could grant faerie wishes, but\nwasn't sure it would work for other races.
Are you telling me you hid that from me\nfrom the start?
You half-doubted it anyway, right?\nSo that doesn't really count as tricking you.
Besides, what's there to be mad about?\nIt worked. Everything's fine and dandy.
It is no such thing! I wouldn't have wished\nfor this if I knew it'd be done so forcefully!
Tell me how to undo it.
But that'd be such a waste.
Didn't you get exactly what you wanted?
Not if it meant he got hurt in the process!
Did you ever stop to think he might be\nHAPPIER without all his memories?
Oh, enough scowling already. I really don't\nthink all this is as bad as you're making it\nout to be—for him OR you.

Just bear in mind that if the wish is
undone, anything that happened while
he was suffering from amnesia will be
forgotten.
Of course. It'll be like your wish never\nhappened. Are you at peace with that?
Yes. I'd rather he went back to normal.
*sigh* Fine, then. Let it never be said that\nI leave my ＂customers＂ high and dry.
Here. One more crystal. Stand in front of\nyour prince, wish for his memory to return,\nand you'll be golden.
You yourself proved that my crystals\nwork for dragons. But remember this:
It's not so easy for people to deny what\nlies in their hearts. Can you commit to\nnegating your wish without hesitation?
What splendid resolve. Now, it's about\ntime I took my leave. Farewell to you,\nhuman-like dragon.
Yes... Now I can finally fix this mess.
Wait for me, darling. I'm coming!
